{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":10015,"record_hash":"sha256:c3fa4be528ccee4ab4181fa0accb0ea1077776207ddea5652902562bcbc81304","timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:45:01.470Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"previous_status\":{\"completed\":\"Best prior art: **Claude Code for local session UX**, **Copilot CLI for remote/cross-device continuity**, **Cursor/Windsurf for lightweight “pull past context into this chat”**, and **Aider for simple file-based history**.\\n\\n**Claude Code**\\nSource: [Manage sessions](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/sessions), [How Claude Code works](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/how-claude-code-works)\\n\\n- `claude --continue`: resume most recent session in current directory.\\n- `claude --resume`: open picker.\\n- `claude --resume <name>` / `<session-id>`: direct resume.\\n- `/resume`: switch from inside an active session.\\n- `--from-pr <number>`: resume session linked to a PR.\\n- `/rename`, `claude -n`: name sessions.\\n- `/branch` or `--fork-session`: fork a conversation without mutating original history.\\n- Picker can widen from current worktree to all repo worktrees or all projects on machine.\\n- Shows session name/summary, age, message count, branch, project path.\\n- `/clear`, `/compact`, `/context`: manage context window.\\n- `/export`: export transcript; JSONL stored locally under `~/.claude/projects/...`.\\n\\nGitButler should copy: named sessions, branch/worktree-aware picker, fork-vs-resume distinction, PR-linked resume, previewable transcripts, and explicit local storage/export.\\n\\n**OpenAI Codex**\\nSources: [openai/codex repo](https://github.com/openai/codex), [ChatGPT release notes: Codex remote access](https://help.openai.[REDACTED:entropy])\\n\\nFrom local `codex-cli 0.121.0 --help`:\\n\\n- `codex resume [SESSION_ID] [PROMPT]`: resume by UUID or thread name.\\n- `codex resume --last`: most recent.\\n- `codex resume --all`: disables cwd filtering and shows CWD column.\\n- `codex resume --include-non-interactive`: includes `exec` sessions.\\n- `codex fork [SESSION_ID] [PROMPT]`: fork previous interactive session.\\n- `--remote <ws/wss>`: connect TUI to remote app server.\\n- `codex cloud`: browse cloud tasks and apply changes locally.\\n- Codex app/mobile remote\n[TRUNCATED]\nps://docs.continue.dev/cli/tui-mode)\\n\\n- `cn --resume`: resume previous conversation.\\n- `/resume`: resume previous chat session.\\n- `/fork`: fork from current history.\\n- `/compact`: summarize chat history.\\n- `/title` / `/rename`: set session title.\\n- `/info`: show token/cost/session info.\\n- Restores full conversation history on resume.\\n\\nGitButler should copy: `/info`, `/compact`, `/fork`, and rename/title as first-class controls.\\n\\n**Windsurf**\\nSource: [Cascade overview](https://docs.windsurf.com/windsurf/cascade/cascade)\\n\\n- Continue button resumes trajectory after tool-call limit.\\n- Auto-Continue can keep going automatically.\\n- Named checkpoints and reverts.\\n- Real-time awareness of user actions; user can say “Continue.”\\n- Share conversation for Teams/Enterprise.\\n- `@`-mention previous conversations; retrieves summaries, checkpoints, and relevant parts, usually not full conversation.\\n- Multiple Cascades can run simultaneously; docs recommend worktrees when editing similar files.\\n\\nGitButler should copy: checkpoints with names, partial retrieval from past conversations, “continue trajectory” affordance, and warning/isolation around concurrent agents touching same files.\\n\\n**What GitButler Should Build**\\nPick this stack:\\n\\n1. **Session picker**: name, branch, worktree, project path, last activity, changed files, PR/issue links.\\n2. **Resume vs fork vs reference**: resume mutates same thread, fork copies history, reference injects summarized prior context.\\n3. **Handoff packet**: touched files, commands run, decisions made, test state, branch/worktree, next steps.\\n4. **Git-native checkpoints**: prompt-level snapshots, named checkpoints, revert with scary-clear warnings.\\n5. **Cross-device steering**: live session view, approvals, diffs, test output, keep-awake status.\\n6. **History intelligence**: standup summary, “what was I doing?”, friction-derived instruction suggestions.\\n7. **Exportable local truth**: Markdown export plus structured local store. Keep it inspectable.\"}}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:45:01.470Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}